reason.tex:
%text For $x > \frac\pi{4}, \sin x > \cos x$. Which is why % \[ \quad f(x) = \begin{cases}
\cos x - \sin x, x \in \left(0, \frac\pi{4} \right) \\ \sin x - \cos x, x \in \left(\frac\pi{4}, \frac\pi{2} \right) \end{cases} \] %text And hence, at $x = \frac{\pi}{3}$ % \begin{align}
f'(x) &= \ddx \left(\sin x-\cos x \right) = \cos x + \sin x\\ \text{or } f' \left(\frac\pi{3} \right) &= \frac{\sqrt{3} + 1}{2} \end{align} %text %
